The paper deals with compressed sensing and signal recovery, which are core topics in information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SP). The use of total variation minimization and Haar wavelet transform also suggests a connection to machine learning (cs.LG) and numerical analysis (cs.NA). Finally, the focus on non-uniform recovery and breaking sample complexity barriers may also fall under the scope of statistical learning theory (cs.SI).
